specifically sought nor specifically avoided, b=
y a seeker of Self. If Nature 
gives one some siddhi(s), one should accept =
them with neither excitement nor 
disappointment. But one should NOT run af=
ter them, for they are neither 
necessary nor sufficient for self-realizati=
on and liberation.
