<DIV align=3Dleft><FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=
=3DVerdana>Let us use the analogy of climbing a hill. Climbing hill is one'=
s spiritual sadhana. Reaching the top is liberation. Different people climb=
 the hill from different sides and using different paths. There may be tree=
s with nice fruits on the sides of the road. They are siddhis or special ab=
ilities.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=3Dleft><FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=
=3DVerdana> </FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=3Dleft><FONT color=3D#000000 size=
=3D2 face=3DVerdana>If one gets distracted, starts climbing the trees and c=
ollecting fruits, one's journey gets delayed and one may not reach the top.=
 That is why Vasishtha says a seeker of Self does not pursue any siddhis.</=
FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=3Dleft><FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana=
> </FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=3Dleft><FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=
=3DVerdana>But if some fruits fall in one's lap by themselves, one can keep=
