<DIV align=3Dleft><FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3D=
Verdana>Here, some people swayed by siddhis may be tempted to use one's sid=
dhis to judge how high one climbed. But that is faulty. One person who reac=
hed the absolute top may not have any fruits, while one person who still ha=
s ways to climb may have gotten some really nice fruit. Using externaslly d=
emonstrable siddhis that are neither necessary nor sufficient for Self-real=
ization as a measure of one's progress is unsound.</FONT></DIV>
